 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "MetalTreatmentAdvisor ⊣ Metal Treatment, Coating & Machining Plant
 Operations Governor, langgraph-clj StateGraph, append-only audit
 ledger. A plant OPERATIONS COORDINATION actor for a metal-treatment/
 coating/machining job shop (electroplating -> anodizing ->
 heat-treatment -> CNC machining production line) producing
 electroplated, anodized, powder-coated, galvanized, heat-treated and
 precision-machined parts -- not direct plating/machining-line-
 equipment control authority. Four ops (`:log-production-batch` /
 `:schedule-maintenance` / `:flag-safety-concern` /
 `:coordinate-shipment`), all `:effect :propose` only. Ten concrete
 governor checks elaborate this blueprint's four HARD invariants:
 propose-only effect, closed op allowlist, closed proposal-effect
 allowlist (no direct plating/machining-line-equipment control),
 permanent plating/machining-line-actuate block, independent equipment
 verification/registration before maintenance scheduling, independent
 batch verification/registration before shipment coordination,
 independent shipment-weight recompute against the batch's own logged
 weight, double-schedule guard, product-category validation, and
 defect-rate plausibility validation. Safety-concern flagging
 (electroplating-bath chemical-toxicity exposure -- cyanide/hexavalent-
 chromium/acid baths, CNC-machining swarf/cutting-tool laceration
 hazard, heat-treatment-furnace burn/radiant-heat exposure)
 ALWAYS escalates to a human shop supervisor; `:log-production-batch`
 is the only op eligible to auto-commit, and only at phase 3 when
 governor-clean."}
